<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78824bd2-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s80c–2"><num value="80c–2">§ 80c–2.</num><heading> Authorization of appropriations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For fiscal year 1982, and for each of the three succeeding fiscal years, there are hereby authorized to be appropriated such amounts as may be necessary and appropriate to carry out the provisions and purposes of this chapter. Any sums so appropriated shall remain available until expended.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id78824bd3-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/pl/96/477/tV/s504">Pub. L. 96–477, title V, § 504</ref>, <date date="1980-10-21">Oct. 21, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/2292">94 Stat. 2292</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id78824bd4-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id78824bd5-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="id78824bd6-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1981-01-01">Jan. 1, 1981</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/96/477/s507">section 507 of Pub. L. 96–477</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t15/s80c">section 80c of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
